qa_pairs.text_input: Who are the stakeholders of the FDA Office of Women's Health (OWH)?
qa_pairs.output: The stakeholders of the FDA Office of Women's Health (OWH) include national associations, community organizations, businesses, health care providers, colleges and universities, researchers, policy-makers, media and information outlets, and anyone interested in promoting women's health.

qa_pairs.text_input: How can I get free publications from the FDA Office of Women's Health (OWH)?
qa_pairs.output: You can get free publications from the FDA Office of Women's Health (OWH) by ordering them online or by calling the OWH toll-free number at 1-800-FDA-1088.

qa_pairs.text_input: What topics are addressed in the fact sheets, brochures, and medicine booklets offered by the FDA Office of Women's Health (OWH)?
qa_pairs.output: The fact sheets, brochures, and medicine booklets offered by the FDA Office of Women's Health (OWH) address a wide range of health topics including safe medication use, heart disease, HIV, HPV, menopause, birth control, and more.
